        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p>Dear Sir!</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I received your favor of the 8<hi rend="sup">th</hi>
                <add>?</add><lb/> but have not received as yet the package from
                Ada<add>ms</add><lb/> Express. This is to thank you for both and to<lb/> inform you,
                dear Sir! what you will be glad to hear<lb/> that there is at last good prospect of
                a union bet<add>ween</add><lb/> two of our congregations, the matter has been urged
                    <add>on</add><lb/> both sides and as far as I have a hand in, it
                    sha<add>ll</add><lb/> not fail again. For this reason please also to<lb/>
                discontinue the advertisement in your Occiden<add>t.</add>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I will bring before next meeting your bill<lb/> with $2.80<lb/> for
                the circulars, and for advertisement 2.60<lb/> being for one insertion $5.40/</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I cannot promise you to get new subscribers for<lb/> your Occident
                &amp; Bible though, when the latter work wi<add>ll</add><lb/> be finished I might
                sell 2 or 3 copies of 5; you have Messr<lb/>
                <persName>Abeles</persName> &amp; <persName>Tanssig</persName> and myself among the
                list of subscribers<lb/> (to be sent bound, when complete) on whom you may rely.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I am, dear sir, your affectionate and humble<lb/>
                <persName role="author">Isidore Bush</persName><lb/></p>
            <p><placeName>Carondelet</placeName>
                <date>October 1<hi rend="sup">st</hi> 5613</date>.<lb/>
                <add>Hebrew</add>
            </p>
        </body>
